Cream butter or margarine with powdered sugar until light. Mix in brandy and water. Chop almonds and set 1/2 cup aside. Add the rest of the almonds to mixture. Stir in flour and mix well. Chill dough until stiff enough to mold. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Shape dough into crescent shapes (Use about 1 teaspoon per cookie.) Dip into additional chopped almonds Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 12 - 15 minutes. Cool on wire racks about 5 minutes. Option: Roll gently in additional powdered sugar after cooling.